<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 13 at 1:48PM MDT  by NWS Saltlake</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of west central
Garfield and east central Iron Counties through 230 PM MDT...
At 147 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles northwest of Panguitch, or 25 miles south of Beaver, moving
north at 10 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of west central
Garfield and east central Iron Counties.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
